## §4: Customer-side decision card

*Drop-in for Kit B customer walkthrough. Sentence case, active voice, no em-dashes.*

---

### Which plan works for you?

| | Order now | Week plan | Month plan |
|---|---|---|---|
| **What you commit to** | One meal today | 3 meals this week | 12 meals over 4 weeks |
| **What you save** | No discount | 15% off your whole order | 20% off your whole order |
| **What you pay** | At pickup | Half now, half over the week | Everything upfront |
| **When you eat** | Today | This week, your schedule | Across the next 4 weeks, your schedule |
| **Best for** | Trying it out | Weekly regulars who want a deal | Regular eaters who want the most savings |
| **Example savings (per meal)** | $13.50 | $11.47 (save $2.03) | $10.80 (save $2.70) |
| **Example savings (total)** | none | $6.08 on 3 meals | $32.40 on 12 meals |
| **LB account needed?** | No | Yes ($5/year) | Yes ($5/year) |

---

**Order now**
No commitment required. Order one meal, pick it up today, pay at pickup. This is the easiest way to try a new food truck. No account needed.

**Start week plan**
Pick 3 meals for this week. Pay half now, half over the week. You lock in 15% off every one of those meals compared to the walk-up price. You pick which days. You can change times within the week if plans shift (Atlas handles it). LB membership ($5/year) required.

**Start month plan**
Pick 12 meals spread over the next 4 weeks. Pay everything upfront and get 20% off every meal. The third meal is nearly free. You choose your days when you sign up. Missed meals roll forward up to 7 days, then go to the community pool for SNAP-recipient free meals. LB membership ($5/year) required.

---

**CTA row:**

| | **Order one meal** | **Start week plan** | **Start month plan** |
|---|---|---|---|

---

